hic and nerfs - long</span><hr size=1> Well Luna it's been great having you as a guildmate. I'll miss you! I wish you'd think on it at least another week before you quit outright but if not, hope to see you in another game down the road somewhere. <br>
<br>
I think all you needed to say in your first post was Mez defines a Sorcerer and Stealth defines an Assassin and you pretty much point out whats wrong with DAOC in general. There are 2 really good classes in the game as a whole and a handfull of others that are good ,the rest stink.<br>
<br>
Stealth was really handled badly in general. It's not stealth it's invisibility. My only real issues with it have/had been.<br>
<br>
1. No one had counters to it. (i.e melees having detect ambush that does a /face when it goes off. Still doesn't make stealther visable just lets you know somethings up in that direction.)<br>
<br>
2. It works when it shouldn't. If an hunter hits you and you see him and start whacking and he runs hits his speed burst how is it that he stealths when he is still in your line of sight?<br>
<br>
If they were gonna spring this on you they should have offered a way for infs to escape similar to the hunter/ranger speed thing. I think non detected when killing was a bad idea to begin with but they should have offered something in return.<br>
<br>
Stealth shouldn't solely Define an assassin class the amount of damage he can do to a target and his ability to escape should figure in as prominently.  Stealth should just be Just one tool of many that aid the assassin in his work.<br>
<br>
I think the Game is essentially missing lots of utility spells that would make it more fun. Invis, detect invis, dispel magic. Basically as creepy said before it lacks counters. The Stungard mez strategy alone has made melee types useless in RvR(except Skalds) it never required the nerf it got just give a fair amount of classes dispel magic. Most times counters get called nerfs when they aren't in the mez instance it would be a nerf if you gave every class that can cast a spell a huge AE Dispel magic. If you give a single dispel to casters and healers and maybe give an AE to classes like Sorc,Spiritmaster and Enchanter it's not so big.<br>
<br>
Well thats all the ranting I have in me for the day. If you haven't already please consider it some more before you cancel your accounts Luna.<br>
<br>
